    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.27.67-68_0001"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">Neihardt Collection</note>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">67</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>March 16, 1959</dateline>
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Route 7</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Columbia, Missouri</addrLine>
                    </address>
                
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I was quite overcome this morning to find a copy of <hi rend="underline">Divine Enchantment</hi> in my mailbox. It is an item I scarcely dared hope I would ever own, and will spur me on to make my little "<del>n</del><add>N</add>eihardt Collection" as complete as possible. You are very kind, indeed, and I thank you for your generous and gracious favor.</p>
                
                <p>For some years the reading of your western epic has been a source of pleasure and inspiration to me. However, I must say that your reading opened my ears and eyes to much that was hidden, and I have since been reading again, with new understanding. Perhaps it is partly due also to the circumstance that I am getting older, and your poetry, like the great poetry of all ages, means mor<del>d</del><add>e</add> as more experience is brought to it.</p>
                
                <p>I count my meeting with you as one of the great renewing experiences of my life. Thank you.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely,</salute>
                
                    <signed>Martin Schmitt</signed>
                
                    <signed>Martin Schmitt</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
            
            <div1 type="envelope">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.27.67-68_0002"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">68</fw>
                
                <ab type="return">
                    <hi rend="caps">UNIVERSITY OF OREGON
                        <lb/>
                    THE LIBRARY
                        <lb/>
                    EUGENE, OREGON</hi>
                </ab>
                
                <ab type="postmark">
                    EUGENE
                    MAR 16
                    4 PM
                    1959
                    OREG.
                
                    GIVE
                    RED CROSS
                    FUND
                </ab>
